  "prompt": "Can I ever get a free domain name?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several ways to get a free domain name, though they often come with limitations:\n\n1. Free Subdomain Options:\n- Blogger\n- WordPress.com\n- GitHub Pages\n- Google Sites\n- Wix\n- Weebly\n\n2. Free Domain Name Services:\n- Freenom (offers free .tk, .ml, .ga, .cf, and .gq domains)\n- No-IP (free dynamic DNS)\n- DuckDNS (free dynamic DNS)\n\n3. Promotional Offers:\n- Some web hosting companies occasionally offer free domain names with hosting plans\n- Domain registrars sometimes provide free domains for the first year\n\nLimitations of Free Domains:\n- Limited customization\n- Less professional appearance\n- Potential ads\n- Less credible for business websites\n- Renewal might require payment\n- Less SEO-friendly\n\nRecommendations:\n- For professional websites, consider purchasing a domain\n- Paid domains are typically more reliable and credible\n- Typical domain costs range from $10-$15 per year\n\nIf you're just experimenting or creating a personal project, free domains can be a good starting point.",
